Ayonae Ro<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sandrakspiritwalker>Sandrak Spiritwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/03 2:27:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4829.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.attrition.org/eq/sigs/granthor.jpg HEIGHT=160 WIDTH=140 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: will my gear be good enough?</span><hr size=1> Just be prepared and make sure whomever is healing you is prepared.  At level 57 with your gear in PoV you are gonna take a beating.  You can still tank them just fine, you just need to make sure your healers know how many hps you have so they can time heals properly.<br>
<br>
I have found myself asking this same question recently.  I have applied to and been allowed to raid with a guild full of warriors who have gear that so far outclasses mine its not even funny.  I have been worried that I am gonna soak too much mana, die when I shouldnt, etc.<br>
<br>
There are times when gear matters alot.  There are more times when having a good head on your shoulders, following instructions and not panicing will mean more than any gear you can possibly ever attain.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion, I can be and am wrong more often than not, so take it with a grain of salt. <p><table width="50%" border="0">
