if ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  PoP exp groups are all about the healers. As tanks, our job hasn't really changed. Hold aggro, period. Damage dealers, same thing.... do damage, try not to steal aggro.<br>
<br>
Clerics have really impressed me over the past couple months, especially after I got flagged and left the Plane of Karnor (errrr nightmare). <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  My hp in full buffs is around the 6400 mark right now, and the only time I've come across mobs that gave me the impression a better tank was needed were some of the giants in storms. Those suckers hit hard and have nasty procs to boot, plus they mitigate slows. I was parsing a few of them at 190 dps (average throughout the fight, slowed and unslowed periods combined). I dropped a few times that night hehe. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443380" target="_blank">Daxos Valdorn</a><br>
